[Since the start of the HPAI H5N8 event in France, reportedly on 25 Nov 2016, 484 outbreaks have been reported to the OIE as of 4 Apr 2017 (date of the submission of the most recent follow-up report No. 30). An interactive map showing all outbreaks is available at http://www.oie.int/wahis_2/public/wahid.php/Reviewreport/Review/viewsummary?fupser=&dothis=&reportid=21772.

The most recent, updated Outbreak Assessment of "Highly Pathogenic Avian Influenza H5N8 in the UK and Europe" by UK DEFRA's Veterinary & Science Policy Advice Team - International Disease Monitoring (No. 13, 5 Apr 2017) is available at https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/607559/uoa-avian-flu-europe-update13.pdf.

Subscribers are encouraged to visit the exhaustive French overview "Epidemiological status of HPAI viruses from the clade 2.3.4.4. in Europe since October 2016: situation point on 10 Apr 2017," (on-line English translation is enabled), which includes several useful maps and figures, available at http://www.plateforme-esa.fr/article/situation-epidemiologique-des-virus-iahp-issus-du-clade-2344-en-europe-depuis-octobre-2016-0. - Mod.AS

A HealthMap/ProMED-mail map can be accessed at: https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=4976572,100.]
